Turkish Equity Movers: Deva, Goodyear, Koza Altin, THY Move

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-03-18T12:51:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/turkish-equity-movers-deva-goodyear-koza-altin-thy-move.html
Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  fell 573.03, or 0.9 percent, to 62,909.12 at the 12:30
p.m. break in trading in Istanbul.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.    Deva Holding AS (DEVA)  , a pharmaceuticals company, rose
after saying its full-year loss narrowed last year to 1.6
million liras ($1 million) from 8.2 million liras in 2009. The
shares gained 5 kurus, or 1.8 percent, to 2.77 liras. The
company announced 2010 results after the markets closed
yesterday.    Goodyear Lastikleri Turk AS (GOODY)  , the Turkish unit of
Goodyear Tire & Rubber Co., climbed 70 kurus, or 2.2 percent,
after saying it would seek to reduce a demand for backtaxes and
fines to 8.96 million liras from 47.4 million liras. The company
will apply within two weeks to pay the reduced fine under the
government’s restructuring program, it said after the markets
closed yesterday.    Koza Altin Isletmeleri AS (KOZAL)  , a gold miner, jumped
50 kurus, or 2.3 percent, to an all-time high of 22.10 liras as
gold prices surged $16.30 to $1,420.50 an ounce. Goldman Sachs
said in a research note that gold was set to rally toward its 3-
month price target of $1,480 an ounce.    Turk Hava Yollari (THYAO)  AO (THYAO), the national airline, lost 9
kurus, or 2 percent, to 4.47 liras after the United Nations
announcement that it would take action in Libya helped send
crude oil prices back up to $103.10 a barrel in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Ankara 
